1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on the integration of deep learning with automated theorem proving, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and computational linguistics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel approach for embedding logical formulae using DAG LSTMs, which is a deep learning technique commonly used in AI research. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of graph-structured representations and deep learning methods for embedding logical formulae, which are both topics within the field of machine learning. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - While not the main focus of the paper, the use of graph-structured representations and deep learning methods for image analysis and recognition falls under the scope of computer vision. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for embedding logical formulae, which falls under the scope of neural computing.
